==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conciliable
<hw>Con*cil"i*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conciliabulum</ets>, fr. <ets>concitium</ets> assembly: cf. F.
<ets>conciliabule</ets>. See <er>Council</er>.]</ety> <def>A small or
private assembly, especially of an ecclesiastical nature.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conciliable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Conciliable
<hw>Con*cil"i*a*ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>conciliable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being conciliated or
reconciled.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conciliabule</ent>⟦br⟧
